<div style=3D"float: right;padding-top:2pt"></div><h1 id=3D"hid1" class=3D"=
section">Geometric distribution</h1>
<p class=3D"author">by <span itemprop=3D"author" itemscope=3D"" itemtype=3D=
"https://schema.org/Person"><a class=3D"author" id=3D"article-author" href=
=3D"https://www.statlect.com/about/#author">Marco Taboga</a></span>, PhD</p=
>
<p>
   The geometric distribution is the probability distribution of the number=
 of
   failures we get by repeating a Bernoulli experiment until we obtain the =
first
   success.
</p>



<p><img width=3D"29" height=3D"24" src=3D"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgo=
AAAANSUhEUgAAAB0AAAAYCAIAAACJPGHrAAAAAXNSR0IArs4c6QAAAARnQU1BAACxjwv8YQUAAA=
AJcEhZcwAADsMAAA7DAcdvqGQAAABJSURBVEhLY/z//z8DDQATlKY2GGrmgsL3yJEjUB4Dg42ND=
ZBEFiEeQPRCwGj4QsBQS7+j6QECRtMDBIymBwgYTQ8QMLTMZWAAAEw6JxXCQPIuAAAAAElFTkSu=
QmCC" alt=3D"Table of Contents" style=3D"vertical-align:-12px;cursor:pointe=
r"></p> =20
<div class=3D"clps" id=3D"table-of-contents"><div class=3D"tableOfContents"=
>
<p><span class=3D"tocTitle">Table of contents</span></p>
<ol><li><p><a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/probability-distributions/ge=
ometric-distribution#hid2">Intuition</a></p></li><li><p><a href=3D"https://=
www.statlect.com/probability-distributions/geometric-distribution#hid3">Def=
inition</a></p></li><li><p><a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/probability-=
distributions/geometric-distribution#hid4">Relation to the Bernoulli distri=
bution</a></p></li><li><p><a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/probability-d=
istributions/geometric-distribution#hid5">Expected value</a></p></li><li><p=
><a href=3D"https://www.statlect.com/probability-distributions/geometric-di=
stribution#hid6">Variance</a></p></li><li><p><a href=3D"https://www.statlec=
