<h2 id=3D"hid10" class=3D"subsection">The shifted geometric distribution</h=
2>
<p>
   As we have said in the introduction, the geometric distribution is the
   distribution of the <strong>number of failed trials</strong> before the =
first
   success.
</p>
<p>
   The shifted geometric distribution is the distribution of the <strong>to=
tal
   number of trials</strong> (all the failures + the first success).
</p>
<p>
   In other words, if
   <span class=3D"inm"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"13" height=3D"24" src=3D"=
data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAICR=
AEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"X" style=3D"background-position:0px -2565px;vertical-al=
ign:-5px"></span>
   has a geometric distribution, then
   <span class=3D"displayed"><img class=3D"sp" width=3D"81" height=3D"38" s=
rc=3D"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIAAANvf7wAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAE=
AAAICRAEAOw=3D=3D" alt=3D"[eq29]" style=3D"background-position:0px -1874px;=
"></span>has
   a shifted geometric distribution.
</p>
<p>
   It is then simple to derive the properties of the shifted geometric
   distribution.
</p>
<p>
